{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"significand"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The magnitude of a floating-point value ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"F","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can be calculated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by using the following formula, where ","type":"text"},{"code":"**","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is exponentiation:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["x.significand * (F.radix ** x.exponent)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In the next example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has a value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"21.5","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which is encoded as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"1.34375 * 2 ** 4","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The significand of ","type":"text"},{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is therefore 1.34375.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let y: Double = 21.5","// y.significand == 1.34375","// y.exponent == 4","// Double.radix == 2"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If a type’s radix is 2, then for finite nonzero numbers, the significand","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is in the range ","type":"text"},{"code":"1.0 ..< 2.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For other values of ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"x.significand","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is defined as follows:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x.significand"},{"type":"text","text":" is 0.0."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"type":"text","text":" is infinite, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x.significand"},{"type":"text","text":" is infinity."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"type":"text","text":" is NaN, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x.significand"},{"type":"text","text":" is NaN."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The significand is frequently also called the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"mantissa"}]},{"text":", but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"significand is the preferred terminology in the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/servlet/opac?punumber=4610933"},{"text":", to allay confusion with the use of mantissa for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the fractional part of a logarithm.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/FloatingPoint"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/floatingpoint/significand"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"significand"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"}],"externalID":"s:SF11significandxvp","ti